  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Re-establishing basic policing in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To re-establish basic policing in three urban areas in south-central Somalia (Baidoa, Beledweyne and Kismayo) by assisting Somali authorities in recruiting  up to 1,860 additional police officers. This will provide improved security for Somali citizens, particularly women and girls with the additional 1,860 police personnel carrying out basic police functions in three urban areas in south-central Somalia and enable the re-establishment of essential services such as health and education. The programme will also help create the conditions for an African Union Mission in Somalia (AMISOM) exit and handover of basic security responsibilities to Somali security institutions. The programme will independently monitor the quality of policing on the ground and carry out regular local perception surveys to assess whether security in the three towns is improving.</narrative>
  </description>
